# Status beginning with '#' are disabled.

# ---- OPTIONS -----
# ANNOYWARE  (mail | reboot_required | updates_available)
# AUDIT      (ec2_cost | processes | services | users | rcs_cost)
# HARDWARE   (battery | cpu_count | cpu_freq | cpu_temp | disk_io |  fan_speed | load_average | memory | raid | swap disk)
# IDs        (whoami | hostname | ip_address)
# NETWORKING (session | network | wifi_quality)
# OS         (logo | distro | release | arch)
# TIME       (date | time | time_utc | uptime)
# ???        (custom | entropy | apport)
# ------------------

# Tmux has one status line, with 2 halves for status
tmux_left="{% for v in common_byobu_widgets_left %}{{ v }} {% endfor %}"

# You can have as many tmux right lines below here, and cycle through them using Shift-F5
tmux_right="{% for v in common_byobu_widgets_right %}{{ v }} {% endfor %}"
